ticle/details/147099665\"},{\"title\":\"终端福音，AI终端编程助手Aider\",\"url\":\"https://juejin.cn/post/7479225933062651930\"},{\"title\":\"全球首位AI程序员“Devin AI”也许可以把“复制粘贴”\",\"url\":\"http://www.51tkk.com/news/98e399898.html\"},{\"title\":\"ai编程\",\"url\":\"https://raindrop.io/bizhanrensheng/ai-50084580\"}]\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"2026 年 AI 编程工具横评：Copilot / Cursor / Claude Code / Windsurf / Trae，到底该用哪个？（附组合方案）\",\"url\":\"https://juejin.cn/post/7605494530017280040\"},{\"title\":\"2026 年 AI 编程工具横评：Copilot / Cursor / Claude Code / Windsurf / Trae，到底该用哪个？（附组合方案）\",\"url\":\"https://article.juejin.cn/post/7605494530017280040\"},{\"title\":\"我用半天时间，一行代码没写ai的一个开源软件 ”一个仓库，管理所有 AI 工具配置“\",\"url\":\"https://developer.aliyun.com/article/1711553\"},{\"title\":\"@empjs/skill：让 AI SKill 管理变得前所未有的简单\",\"url\":\"https://juejin.cn/post/7597808104463417390\"},{\"title\":\"【中配】Claude Code 崩坏: OpenCode、订阅价格与 AI 编程大洗牌 - Caleb Writes Code\",\"url\":\"https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1nTkVB5EqN\"},{\"title\":\"2025年AI编程工具大爆发：Cursor、Claude Code引领前端开发新纪元\",\"url\":\"https://juejin.cn/post/7570564840428470299\"},{\"title\":\"OpenAI Releases GPT-5-Codex Upgrade to Enhance Programming Agent Performance\",\"url\":\"https://m.sohu.com/a/935524483_122328931/?pvid=000115_3w_a\"},{\"title\":\"Unable to select Codex IDE · Issue #534 · bmad-code-org/ ...\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/bmad-code-org/BMAD-METHOD/issues/534\"},{\"title\":\"2025 年最佳编程智能体：真正帮你开发的工具 · Logto 博客\",\"url\":\"http://www.360doc.cn/article/21539921_1159890106.html\"},{\"title\":\"放弃 Cursor，我依然选择了 Claude 断供后的 Windsurf\",\"url\":\"https://xie.infoq.cn/article/5f893edb51baeb51b5bea04ee\"}]\n\nBased on my search, I wasn't able to find specific February 2025 release notes or changelogs for these AI coding tools. However, I did gather information about notable updates and features from around early 2025. Here's what I found:\n\n## Summary of AI Coding Tool Updates (Early 2025)\n\n### **GitHub Copilot**\n- **Agent Mode** rollout began in VS Code (early 2025)\n- **Copilot Workspace** launched (mentioned as January 2026 in some sources, which may be a typo for 2025)\n- **Premium Requests** mechanism introduced with monthly quotas\n- Support for multiple models including Claude 3.5/3.7 Sonnet, Google Gemini 2.0 Flash, and OpenAI GPT-4o\n- **MCP (Model Context Protocol)** support added for connecting external tools\n\n### **Cursor**\n- **Cursor 2.0** was released in late 2024/early 2025\n- **Composer model** introduced - 4x faster generation\n- **Multi-Agent parallel** support added (up to 8 agents)\n- Shift to credit-based pricing caused community backlash in mid-2025\n- CPU/performance issues noted with large projects\n\n### **Claude Code**\n- **Opus 4.6** mentioned in early 2026 sources (possibly a future release)\n- **Agent Teams** feature for multi-instance coordination\n- **1M token context window** (Beta)\n- **/insights command** added for workflow optimization\n- Pricing: Pro at $20/month, Max plans at $100-$200/month\n\n### **Windsurf (formerly Codeium)**\n- **Cascade Agentic** assistant with deep context awareness\n- Remote indexing for large codebases (1M+ lines)\n- Cross-IDE support (VS Code, JetBrains, Vim/Neovim, Xcode)\n- Workflow automation features\n\n### **Devin (Cognition)**\n- **Devin 2.0** announced with interactive planning mode\n- **Devin Search** for codebase exploration\n- **Devin Wiki** for automatic documentation generation\n- Machine snapshot functionality for state preservation\n\n### **Continue.dev**\n- Open-source autopilot for VS Code and JetBrains\n- Support for multiple LLMs (GPT-4, Claude, local Llama)\n- Autocomplete, Edit, Chat, and Agent modes\n\n### **Aider**\n- Terminal-based AI coding tool\n- Git integration with automatic commit messages\n- Voice coding support\n- Multi-file editing capabilities\n\n---\n\n**Important Note**: The search results contain some inconsistencies with dates (some mentioning 2026 dates for what should be 2025 events). For the most accurate and up-to-date February 2025 changelogs, I recommend checking directly with each tool's official documentation:\n\n- **Claude Code**: docs.anthropic.com\n- **Cursor**: cursor.com or cursor.sh\n- **GitHub Copilot**: github.com/features/copilot\n- **Windsurf**: codeium.com\n- **Devin**: cognition.ai\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific information about any particular tool?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
